args:
Chelle's behavior was all an act—her ＂weapon＂
had, in fact, been deployed by the Empire, so
she used the prince and his allies to rid herself
of it. In exchange for having tricked the party,
the princess offers continued cooperation—
though her face remains as inscrutable as ever.
No! The Gran Criminale!\nMy secret weapon! It's...
It was quite the foe, Sister.
But there's no way something without\na heart or soul could ever defeat us!
Now say your prayers, lady,\nbecause you're next!
No! No no no no noooooo!
A highborn lady like myself should never\nlose to the likes of plebeians like you!\nThis is SO very annoying!
I will not forget this! When next we meet,\nI will tear your PIECES into pieces!
Enough, Chelle. This act grows stale.
Wait, an ACT?! What the devil is that\nsupposed to mean?!
The old Chelle would have ranted and\nraved and exposed her emotions as you\njust did. But the new Chelle? I think not.
Ah, I suppose I did overly chew the\nscenery there. But that's what the howls\nof the defeated sound like, no?
Surely it cooled your ire somewhat?
What in the world are you talking about?
It was intended as a reward.\nDid you not say that you hoped\nto ＂send my smug face packing＂?
How the heck do you know about that?!\nAnd what do you mean, ＂reward＂?
It would seem the princess had us\nin the palm of her hand all along.
Somebody better start making sense,\nor I'm going to get REALLY angry!
Eee hee! The weapon you just destroyed,\ndear Flamewyrm, was in fact not MY\nweapon at all.
The Dyrenell Empire deployed it here to\ndisrupt our materium mining operations.
Yes, I was a bit careless about security,\nwhich allowed them to drop it here.\nIt has been QUITE the little annoyance.
So you tricked us into attacking it\nin your stead?!
Chelle, you should have just ASKED us\nfor help. Why in the world did you go\nto all this trickery and trouble?!
But if I ASKED you to do it, Brother,\nI would be in your debt.
Yer in our damn debt NOW!
You found the device on your own.\nYou attacked the device on your own.\nI owe you nothing.
While I do so appreciate such cunning\nand guile, I'm not too fond of it coming\nat my own expense.
Well, that IS frightening. You must know it\nwas never my intention to anger one of the\nlegendary six Greatwyrms.
How about this? I'll give you some of\nthe abundant mana I now have thanks\nto our supply of materium.
Hm. I agree to your generous offer.\nPerhaps I'll use it to erect a light\ndracolith at the Halidom.
Did this lady just BRIBE a Greatwyrm?!
You do realize that you stand in the\npresence of ANOTHER Greatwyrm, yes?\nHow do you intend to bribe ME?
Oh, don't worry—I have a reward for\nyou that I think you will enjoy.
I am not Jupiter! I will not be bought for\na few shiny baubles and some mana!
My reward for you...is that I shall fully\nacknowledge AND support your\nrelationship with my brother.
From this moment hence, his elder sister\nofficially recognizes your relationship!
Here now! That is rather bold of you!
Y-yes, Mym will NEVER be taken in by\nsuch an obvious, ham-fisted effort!
OH, MY DEAR SISTER-IN-LAW!\nI AM SO VERY HAPPY!
Yes, I thought you might be.
She's sure got the two'a them figured out.
That information network of hers\nis a frightening thing indeed.
Yes, my little cats are very good listeners.\nI trust you'll find them very useful moving\nforward.
Then you'll still cooperate in\nour fight against the Empire?
Of COURSE I will support you, my brother.\nDidn't I tell you that one of my standing\ndoes not break her promises?
Now then, with the Empire's meddlesome\nweapon cleanly dispatched, let us return\nto the palace for an evening of revels!
Bwaaa ha ha ha! Now we're talkin'!\nFood always tastes best when someone\nelse is footin' the bill!
Honestly, you two! Pace yourselves unless\nyou want to end up... Hmm? What now?
And now, ladies and gentlemen, it is time\nfor the grand finale of our party to begin!
While I am ever-so-loath to part ways,\nI fear we are nearly at that hour.\nBut first... Leif? May I have this dance?
Such is my duty as a knight, Princess.
Well, that could not have possibly been\nany more unenthusiastic. Do you truly\ndislike the idea of dancing with me so?
Forgive me. ...Princess, pray permit me\na few moments of bliss as we dance.
Eee hee hee! Yes, that's more like it.
If there is something you wish to say,\nplease just let us be done with it.
You led me about like a hound\non a leash, Princess.
I find myself confused as to how,\nexactly, I should react to this.
I'm both angered by your deception,\nand joyous at seeing how you've grown.
Eee hee hee! Hearing you say that\nis the greatest reward of all!
I have long carried a feeling inside me.\nA feeling that I find very hard to put\ninto the form of words.

For as long as I can remember, I have
wanted to make you feel the same—and
now it seems that my heart's deepest wish
has finally been granted.
Ah, but we are not done here!\nI want you to think more about\nwhat that feeling is. Really THINK.
I want to be scorched in your memory\nuntil the very idea of me is never far\nfrom your thoughts.
THAT, dear Leif, is my true desire.
Then you ought know that your desire\nwas fulfilled long ago, Chelle.
I am a loyal knight of Alberia,\nand a member of the Royal Guard.
My life is the protection of the royal line;\nthat is everything to me. As such, you\nhave not left my thoughts for a moment.
Oh, Leif. You truly don't understand.
But very well! I suppose nothing's worth\ndoing if it isn't something of a challenge.
But mark my words—you WILL come\naround to my way of seeing things.\nI will win out, I promise you.
Brother? May I have the last dance?
While I'm rather sad we can no longer play\nhorsey together, I would still be honored\nif you would twirl me about the floor.
Huh? But this is the last song.
While the curtain may be drawn on this\nparty, new ones will continue to be held.

It is a party of war—with this entire 
continent as its venue! Princess and
prince, dragon and demon alike will
all be swept up in the revels.

A party whose invitation one cannot deny,
and one from which they may not retire. 
One where any who tire of dancing are
defeated and leave the stage.
That is the dance we step to now.
I don't want that kind of fight.
Heh. Here in court, my dear brother,\nsentiment is not something to be\ncommunicated with mere words.
Only those who dance with passion all\nnight can possibly bring freedom to all.
If you cannot continue this dance—if you\ncannot continue to WIN—then you will \naccomplish nothing. You will BE nothing.

Be it protecting your people or leading
a most beloved princess by the hand,
you will fail. So then, my brother, are
you resolved to continue the dance?
If that is truly the fate of royalty, \nthen I will not allow myself to\nbe defeated.
If it means I get to save everyone,\nthen I will never stop this dance!
Oh, I DO like that look in your eyes!\nCome then, brother—let us dance.\nLet us surrender to its flow.
We shall dance this endless rondo,\nbut who will be standing in the center\nof the hall when the music ends?
Heh heh... It would seem that we\nhave found the limit of the Auspex.

The time grows near—the time where all
I have lost shall be drawn into the light.
The time in which the vile blood shall
fall to despair...
And the time where I will be WHOLE!
Heh heh... AAAAH HA HA HA HA!
